data.name: Label11.Text
data.value: The second and quicker way to place the planets is to use the randomization button. This will fill in the remaining planets based on randomization. planets will be added until the maximum number of planets has been reached.

data.name: Label10.Text
data.value: There are two ways to place planets in the galaxy. The first is a manual way where planets can be placed by either clicking on the grid cell or by setting the X and Y coordinates and clicking "Add planet".

data.name: lblSetupHeader.Text
data.value: When the game is first loaded or reset button is clicked, the screen shows the Setup group box. Within this area, the user can set some basic preferences. The maximum number of planets sets an upper limit to the number of planets exist in the grid based galaxy. The number of shots is an indication of the numbr of times the deathstar can be fired therefore the power of th local sun is permanently drained.
